The next day, at the earliest streak of dawn, he pro- ceeded to the cavern. He found its entrance under im- mense rocks which the tree of Jupiter has covered with its branches. On the threshold of the chasm, he im- molates a black sheep which he offers as a sacrifice to powerful Cybele. Then, he burns the thuja and the cypress in honor of Erebus and of the divinities of the dark shores.
